document_data.Rumors & Legends:
Some claimed that a deepspawn dwelled within the jungle of [[Jundarwood]], though throughout [[Faerûn]]ian history deepspawn were often a source of blame for strange happenings.{{Cite polyhedron/129/Elminster's Everwinking Eye: The Border Kingdoms|11}}

Some hunters and sages in the [[Border Kingdoms]] voiced suspicion that [[Bloutar]]rans had installed a deepspawn within a cave in the forest north of their town as it seemed that those townspeople always came back from a [[stag]] hunt with two or more prizes in hand.{{Cite polyhedron/116/Elminster's Everwinking Eye: The Border Kingdoms: Blackbarn and Bloutar|11}}

Around [[1479 DR]], it was rumored that the farmer [[Nars Thormil]], who lived near [[Wheloon]] in [[Cormyr]], used a deepspawn he had captured to duplicate [[thimdror]]s and sell them to the best eateries in [[Saerloon]] and other nearby settlements.{{Cite dungeon/194/Eye on the Realms: Thormil's Secret|30-31}}
